For a uniform distribution on `Fin (n + 1)`, each element has probability `1 / (n + 1)`. Therefore, `Pr[=x | P] = 1 / (n + 1)` and `Pr[=y | P] = 1 / (n + 1)`. Since these are equal, the goal holds.

